'''''Rebel Charge at Chickamauga''''' is [[computer wargame]] published in 1987 by [[Strategic Simulations]].

==Gameplay==
''Rebel Charge at Chickamauga'' is a game in which the [[Battle of Chickamauga]] in the American Civil War is simulated in a turn-based game.<ref name="CGW40"/>

==Reception==
M. Evan Brooks reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "User-friendly, Chickamauga is an accurate rendition of the Battle of Chickamauga as it began."<ref name="CGW40">{{cite magazine |last=Brooks |first=M. Evan |title=Rebel Charge at Chickamauga: "Make The Right Wing Strong" |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=October 1987 |volume=1 |issue=40 |pages=32–33, 35}}</ref>

Mike Siggins reviewed ''Rebel Charge at Chickamauga'' for ''[[Games International]]'' magazine, and gave it 3 stars out of 5, and stated that "''Chickamauga'' is a good, well balanced game using an established and no doubt familiar system. If the period interests you it should be a recommended purchase, but I am left with a feeling of having to use an old style dial phone when there are push button systems on the market."<ref name="gi12">{{cite journal | last = Siggins |first = Mike | title =Computer Games | journal = [[Games International]] | issue = 12 | pages =47–48 |date=January 1990}}</ref>

